metadata.name: Extinction of the Dinosaurs #18
metadata.description: After a 175 million year stint roaming the Earth, the Dinosaurs of the Cretaceous Period suffered a mass extinction event that wiped out most living things on the planet. There's not enough evidence to thoroughly prove the particulars of how the extinction occurred but it seems in a short time lethal environmental cataclysms took place all over the globe including a potential killer asteroid impact or severe volcanic eruptions.
